Package: EcoPast
Type: Package
Title: Methods and Tools for Deep-Time Macroecology with Fossil Data
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Francesco Carotenuto, Mirko Di Febbraro, Silvia Castiglione, Carmela Serio, Alessandro Mondanaro, Marina Melchionna, Pasquale Raia
Maintainer: Francesco Carotenuto <francesco.carotenuto@unina.it>
Description: Methods to perform macroecological analyses with the fossil record. Actually, EcoPast allows users to perform MInOSSE, a model-based method to reconstruct species geographic ranges by simply relying on the spatial distribution of coeval fossil species  as model predictors. This method is particulary useful when dealing with fossil species that lived during time periods for which no bioclimatic variables are available.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
